      <memberdef kind="function" id="group__dns__sd_1gaeba098fa6d159067c70588cb60056277" prot="public" static="no" const="no" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="non-virtual">
        <type><ref refid="stdbool_8h_1abb452686968e48b67397da5f97445f5b" kindref="member">bool</ref></type>
        <definition>bool dns_sd_is_service_type_enumeration</definition>
        <argsstring>(const struct dns_sd_rec *rec)</argsstring>
        <name>dns_sd_is_service_type_enumeration</name>
        <param>
          <type>const struct <ref refid="structdns__sd__rec" kindref="compound">dns_sd_rec</ref> *</type>
          <declname>rec</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Check if <emphasis>rec</emphasis> is a DNS-SD Service Type Enumeration. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>DNS-SD Service Type Enumeration is used by network tooling to acquire a list of all mDNS-advertised services belonging to a particular host on a particular domain.</para>
<para>For example, for the domain &apos;.local&apos;, the equivalent query would be &apos;_services._dns-sd._udp.local&apos;.</para>
<para>Currently, only the &apos;.local&apos; domain is supported.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="see"><para><ulink url="https://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/html/rfc6763#section-9">Service Type Enumeration, RFC 6763</ulink>.</para>
</simplesect>
<parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>rec</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>the record to in question </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>true if <emphasis>rec</emphasis> is a DNS-SD Service Type Enumeration </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
